{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"alias":"emerald-wood-halcyon","creation_channel":"cli","description":"## Why\n\n`src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/outbound_differ.py` is 855 LOC, over the 800 module-size soft cap and grandfathered on the allowlist (ceiling 862). Graduate it off the allowlist by extracting the cohesive assignee-resolution cluster along the seam docs/architecture.md records for this file (identity-mapping fast-path + 3-tuple /user/search assignee-resolution + `_USER_SEARCH_METHODS` -> `outbound_assignee.py`).\n\n## What\n\nExtract the identity-mapping / assignee-resolution cluster (a genuine call-cluster: `_resolve_assignee_account_id` -> `_bootstrap_account_id_via_user_search` / `_identity_jira_account_id` / `_identity_email`, plus the `_USER_SEARCH_METHODS` constant) into a new leaf module `outbound_assignee.py` (same package). It is a leaf: it imports `rebar._commands.identity` lazily inside its functions and nothing from `outbound_differ`. This mirrors the three existing sibling extractions (`outbound_comments.py`, `outbound_fields.py`, `outbound_links.py`).\n\n`outbound_differ.py` imports the 5 moved symbols back from `outbound_assignee` and RE-EXPORTS them (`# noqa: F401`) so `outbound_differ.<symbol>` keeps resolving — load-bearing for `_bootstrap_account_id_via_user_search` (tests/unit/rebar_reconciler/test_identity_264f_resolve.py) and for the internal `_resolve_assignee_account_id` call. `_rebar_env` and everything else STAY. Pure refactor, no behavior change.\n\nThen graduate the file off the gate: remove its row from `.github/module-size-allowlist.txt` AND `.github/module-size-ceilings.txt`, and delete its `docs/architecture.md` remedy row.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `outbound_assignee.py` exists, is between 100 and 800 LOC, contains the moved assignee cluster (verify: `wc -l src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/outbound_assignee.py`)\n- [ ] `outbound_differ.py` is <= 800 LOC (verify: `wc -l src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/outbound_differ.py`)\n- [ ] `outbound_differ.py` is absent from BOTH `.github/module-size-allowlist.txt` and `.github/module-size-ceilings.txt`, and its `docs/architecture.md` remedy row is deleted (verify: `! grep outbound_differ .github/module-size-allowlist.txt .github/module-size-ceilings.txt`)\n- [ ] `tests/unit/test_module_size_contract.py` passes\n- [ ] The reconciler suite is green with no behavior change (verify: `pytest tests/unit/rebar_reconciler -q`)\n- [ ] Back-compat: `outbound_differ._bootstrap_account_id_via_user_search` and `outbound_differ._resolve_assignee_account_id` still resolve as module attributes (re-exported)\n\n## Notes\nLanded as its own Gerrit change (LLM-Review +1 AND Verified +1) before close. Mechanical/behavior-preserving refactor, so E5 testing-plan is not-applicable (existing reconciler tests are the oracle).","id":"a606-7145-427a-4591","parent_id":"716f-b917-9fc8-41f5","priority":1,"tags":["module-size"],"ticket_type":"story","title":"Split outbound_differ.py: extract assignee resolution into outbound_assignee.py"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1784396305244640001,"uuid":"4a158df5-ea29-4d50-9c72-25be97e5320f"}